-- Indian shares fall for second consecutive session; IT stocks hit
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 06:03AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 7 (Reuters) - India's NSE index fell for a second consecutive session on Thursday as IT stocks such as Infosys <INFY.NS> fell after global rival Cognizant Technology Solutions Corp <CTSH.O> cut its annual revenue guidance.

The broader NSE index <.NSEI> provisionally lost 0.27 percent.